Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_enable_...h_clock_gating(25.10)  timing_enable_...h_clock_gating(25.10)

Name
       timing_enable_latency_through_clock_gating

Syntax
       timing_enable_latency_through_clock_gating

       {true | false}

       Default: true

       Allows propagation of latency phases across clock gating elements.

       When  set  to  true,  the  software allows propagation of clock latency
       phase across clock gating elements.

       When set to false, the software suppresses propagation of clock latency
       across clock gating elements from the enable pin. The enable pin of the
       clock gating element should not be in the clock network for  any  other
       clocks.  This  is  not recommended because the enable path (through the
       'inferred' clock gates, such as, AND, NAND, OR) is either for clock la-
       tency or data paths. If the gated clock check is met, then  the  enable
       should not pass through to the output.

       In case of ICGs, there is no arc from the EN to the CLKOUT on ICGs that
       have  an  incoming enable signal latched. In case of ICG/AND, using the
       enable path may not be correct for determining latency paths. If no la-
       tency paths are found, then the generated clocks definition  will  need
       to be re-checked.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

